d that it is possible to come out of that place courageous, beautiful, and strong.\n\n- Anna White, Mended: Thoughts on Life, Love, and Leaps of Faith\n|\nYou may avoid the risk of a car accident if you avoid driving, but you will lose the joy and freedom of driving.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nSometimes, hope is even harder to bear than grief.\n\n- Claudia Gray, A Million Worlds with You\n|\nIo mi sono sempre lasciata attraversare dalle emozioni, investire con rabbiosa furia, ferirmi nella tormentosa lotta alla sopravvivenza.\n\n- Vanessa Vescera, Le parole di una Rosa\n|\nIt is Vitaraag vignan [the Spiritual Science of the Enlightened Ones] to look at gain, and to see losses is the knowledge of worldly wanderings.\n\n- Dada\n|\nHarry,' Bob drawled, his eye lights flickering smugly, 'what you know about women, I could juggle.\n\n- Jim Butcher, Storm Front\n|\nCompatibility doesn't determine the fate of a marriage, how you deal with the incompatibilities, does.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Wise Mating: A Treatise on Monogamy\n|\nJust when you thought you knew everything about someone, they had to go one better.\n\n- Lindsey Kelk, What a Girl Wants\n|\nHe who is in love is wise and is becoming wiser, sees newly every time he looks at the object beloved, drawing from it with his eyes and his mind those virtues which it possesses.\n\n- Ralph\n|\nPoetry had always seemed something I could turn to in need - an emergency exit, a lifebuoy, as well as a justification.\n\n- John Fowles, The Magus\n|\nThe reason why people do not have price tags is, because life is priceless.\n\n- Gift\n|\nRose unearthed three crystal goblets that almost matched, and even found a tablecloth that hadn't been attacked by moths since its last public appearance.\n\n- Elizabeth C. Bunce, A Curse Dark as Gold\n|\nIf the bee disappeared off the face of the earth, man would only have four years left to live.\n\n- Maurice Maeterlinck, The Life of the Bee\n|\nDisappointment came to me,and booted me,and bruised and hurt 