rything go away. The world doesn't feel like a bigger, brighter place because my hair smells like coconuts.\n\n- Jolene\n|\nOut of love,No regrets--Though the goodnessBe wasted forever.Out of love,No regrets--Though the returnBe never.\n\n- Langston Hughes, Selected Poems\n|\nRich people don’t work for money, but work passionately until the end of their lives\n\n- Sunday\n|\nEducation helps you to find beauty, but you are responsible to see it.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWe can learn a lot from animals, if we're prepared to accept that they may just know more about life than what we do.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nNu mai trăim un prezent placid, ci suntem prinși cu toții în efortul de a ne pregăti permanent pentru viitor.\n\n- Jean-Claude Carrière, Nu sperați că veți scăpa de cărți\n|\nKnowledge is the Best Weapon, Experience is the Best Teacher,Respect is the Best Admirer, But Life Is the Best Answer\n\n- Look\n|\nSomewhere, excitement waited for me like an uncut cake.\n\n- Lauren Wolk, Wolf Hollow\n|\nSometimes you just have those days where everything goes wrong. But sometimes, and totally unexpectedly, something can go right.\n\n- Leila Sales, This Song Will Save Your Life\n|\nThere is much in this world that hurts us, but if we let pain become our master, we live our lives as slaves.\n\n- Hannah Hart, Buffering: Unshared Tales of a Life Fully Loaded\n|\nWhat we believed, we become.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nLife is doubt,And faith without doubt is nothing but death.\n\n- Miguel\n|\nYou can control the visibility of my name and my popularity, but you cannot control the frequency at which people are quoting me. Truth always rises with time.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nWhen You Live Life Too Early, You Learn Life Too Late.\n\n- O.\n|\nWe are always fascinated with the past, but the future is always brighter.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nLike life, love is a constant adventure and a constant process. It is not a possession.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nA truly successful person is not one who achieves his highest ambitions, but one who enjoys helping others reach theirs.\n\n- Charbel\n|\nIn life, you learned that not all white people are racist, not all black folks are criminals, let's admit it and love one another..\n\n- Werley\n|\nAnd once you've been to this Center, this Truth, you'll know your way everywhere. You are never lost again.\n\n- David Housholder, The Blackberry Bush\n|\nIf through a broken heart God can bring His purposes to pass in the world, then thank Him for breaking your heart.\n\n- Oswald\n|\nWhat they want, of course, isn't what you can give them. What you're selling is the hope you can.\n\n- Rosamund Hodge, Bright Smoke, Cold Fire\n|\nAnd Marianne, who had the knack of finding her way in every house to the library, however it might be avoided by the family in general, soon procured herself a book.\n\n- Jane Austen, Sense and Sensibility"